<dl id="n33019f"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n33" href="#n33019f">N33 (VI.B.4)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n33all.htm#n33019f"> 19(f)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Perrault </blockquote> <dd class="well"><mm class="note">Note: Charles Perrault (1628-1703). French poet, prose writer, and storyteller, a leading member of the Acad&eacute;mie Fran&ccedil;aise, who played a prominent part in a literary controversy known as the <i>querelle des anciens et des modernes</i>. He is best remembered for his collection of fairy stories for children, <cite>Contes de ma M&egrave;re l&apos;Oye</cite> (1697; <cite>Tales of Mother Goose</cite>, 1729).  <br>Raphael transcription: <a name="c15006a" href="c15all.htm#c15006a">VI.C.15:006(a)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
